  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Rheumatoid arthritis is an autoimmune disease. It is an erosive polyarthritis that causes auto-antibodies direct against an individual's own joints and joint spaces.",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Morning stiffness\nPolyarthritis\nof MCP and PIP joints\nDoes NOT involve DIP joints\nWrists, elbows, shoulders, ankles, knees also commonly involved\nUlnar deviation at MTP joints\nSwan neck deformity\nRheumatoid nodules\nMost patients initially diagnosed in the early 50s\nCommon associated conditions in severe cases: pleuritis,\ninterstitial lung disease\n,\npericarditis\n, inflammatory eye disease",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Polyarthritis",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Polyarthritis"
        },
        {
          "text": "Swan neck deformity",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Swan_neck_deformity"
        },
        {
          "text": "interstitial lung disease",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Interstitial_lung_disease"
        },
        {
          "text": "pericarditis",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Pericarditis"
        }
      ]
    },
