    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "Xray affected joints for erosions\nRheumatoid factor (positive in 60% to 70% of patients)\nAnti-cyclic citrullinated peptide (CCP) antibodies (positive in about 70% of patients)\nANA\nConsider\narthrocentesis\nWBC count typically 1,500-20,000",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "arthrocentesis",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Arthrocentesis"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Management": {
      "text": "NSAIDs\nSymptomatic relief without slowing underlying disease\nGlucocorticoids\nConsider intraarticular injection if a single joint is inflammed\nSystemic steroids reserved for moderate-severe flairs\nOpioids\nhave a limited role\nDisease-modifying antirheumatic drug (DMARD)\nCan be started by primary care provider or rheumatologist after ER visit",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "NSAIDs",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/NSAIDs"
        },
        {
          "text": "Glucocorticoids",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Glucocorticoids"
        },
        {
          "text": "Opioids",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Opioids"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Disposition": {
